<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/19 (Thu) Retirement and Leisure Time (Host: Sherry)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=317&amp;p=333#p333"><![CDATA[
Session I<br /><br />What Role Should Work Play in Retirement?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/the-science-behind-behavior/201909/what-role-should-work-play-in-retirement">https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog ... retirement</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1. In your opinion, what is a good age to retire?  How much money do most people need to retire at that age?<br /><br />Q2. How do you fill out a retired day?  Would you plan to work (including part-time or volunteer work) in retirement?  Why or why not?<br /><br />Q3. What do you think is most important in retirement life?  What advice would you give to those who have not prepared for their retirement?<br /><br /> <br />Session II<br />How to Liven Up Leisure Time and Beat Boredom<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/why-bad-looks-good/201908/how-liven-leisure-time-and-beat-boredom">https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog ... at-boredom</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1. Do you think you have enough leisure time?  Are you occupied with obligations and honey-do lists?  What are they?<br /><br />Q2. Do you know any people who feel bored in their leisure time or have “leisure time blues”?  What lifestyles or habits do they usually have?  What is your advice to break the boredom habits?<br /><br />Q3. What is on your bucket list?   What have you completed and what would you still like to achieve?<br /><br />Suggested Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. Free talk<br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. First topic discussion<br />8:10 p.m. --8:40 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table  are invited)<br />8:40 p.m.-- 9.:15 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />9:15 p.m.-- 9:30 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br /><br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Mon Sep 16, 2019 9:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
